    "debase":       { example: "Printing too much money risks debasing the currency and triggering inflation.", exampleJa: "過剰な貨幣印刷は通貨を貶め、インフレを引き起こすリスクがあります。" },
    "decadence":    { example: "The late Roman Empire is often associated with moral decadence and excess.", exampleJa: "後期ローマ帝国は道徳的退廃と放縦としばしば結び付けられます。" },
    "decry":        { example: "Critics decried the proposed law as an attack on freedom of the press.", exampleJa: "批評家たちはその法案を報道の自由への攻撃として非難しました。" },
