    "hierarchy":     { example: "New employees quickly learn the informal hierarchy that shapes who actually makes decisions.", exampleJa: "新入社員は実際に意思決定を行う人物を形作る非公式な階層をすぐに学ぶ。" },

    // ── missing-examples-batch-015 ───────────────────────────────────────────
    "hollow":        { example: "His apology felt hollow because he had made the same mistake three times before.", exampleJa: "彼の謝罪は空虚に感じられた。なぜなら彼は以前にも3回同じ過ちを犯していたからだ。" },
    "homogeneous":   { example: "The committee was criticised for being too homogeneous, lacking diversity of background and perspective.", exampleJa: "委員会は多様な背景と視点を欠く、同質性が高すぎると批判された。" },
